{"schema":"allo-reading-book@1","slug":"351358-how-many","title":"How Many?","description":"Crawling snails, fluttering butterflies, pigs in the mud. This book has so many animals, and more keep joining in. Can you count them all? A simple book about addition.","language":"English","langCode":"en","isRtl":false,"level":"1","orientation":"landscape","authors":["Sudeshna  Shome Ghosh"],"illustrators":["Sayan  Mukherjee"],"originalAuthors":[],"publisher":"Pratham Books","license":"CC BY 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","sourceId":"storyweaver","contentType":"story","source":{"id":"storyweaver","name":"StoryWeaver, Pratham Books","url":"https://storyweaver.org.in/en/stories/351358-how-many"},"cover":{"card":"https://static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/527516/size3/2ce50b116586b7652ec79c738028bc67.jpg","large":"https://static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/527516/size6/2ce50b116586b7652ec79c738028bc67.jpg"},"audio":null,"pages":[{"n":1,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440805/size6/632e0e3ac91731523179a935ddf29a56.jpg","text":"2 snails hear a croak,","words":null},{"n":2,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440807/size6/69a10878c97d80a5e383ef9368356f88.jpg","text":"1 snail tells them a joke.\nHow many snails can you see?","words":null},{"n":3,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440808/size6/6ccf1cb130090371e9e65ee686b154cb.jpg","text":"1 + 2 = 3 snails","words":null},{"n":4,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440809/size6/18b36a4945c56d211a102a4d39e54a7d.jpg","text":"2 fish in the pool,\n3 more fish make\nit a school.\nHow many fish?","words":null},{"n":5,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440810/size6/cbfe1a412cd52e938f356873eda0b2e1.jpg","text":"2 + 3 = 5 fish","words":null},{"n":6,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440811/size6/5a6589ebbc11816d4a55b0979b44ed62.jpg","text":"3 pigs playing in the sun,\n4 pigs join the fun!\nHow many pigs can you see?","words":null},{"n":7,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440812/size6/e594396de6ce60aade93574ae1713e2c.jpg","text":"3 + 4 = 7 pigs","words":null},{"n":8,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440813/size6/d747b7fc42207034ba1ac5fb05b2f790.jpg","text":"4 butterflies flit and fly,\n5 butterflies wave bye-bye.\nHow many butterflies can you see?","words":null},{"n":9,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440814/size6/7c3163e17991ec30fc27c1dab360e35e.jpg","text":"4 + 5 = 9 butterflies","words":null},{"n":10,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440815/size6/eaf46a40719ec52fabd58674cd966264.jpg","text":"5 worms slip and slide,\nHow many worms can you see?\n5 more worms join the ride.","words":null},{"n":11,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440816/size6/a1bb52af860ce9280b050ccdd1e3c805.jpg","text":"5 + 5 = 10 worms","words":null},{"n":12,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440817/size6/35230ff252af05bdd326b12c0875ff37.jpg","text":"10 ants all in a row,\nLook, here come 2 more.\nHow many ants can you see?","words":null},{"n":13,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440818/size6/9a716b59f1b3eb3548616cd3053f2014.jpg","text":"10 + 2 = 12 ants","words":null},{"n":14,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440819/size6/d7cacccdda2c2b9dbcbcad4742f3d7a9.jpg","text":"How many creatures can you count?\nSnail + Fish + Butterfly + Pig + Ant + Worm","words":null},{"n":15,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/440820/size6/f8cd4360cf3728e6e0cf736e787a8fb1.jpg","text":"1\n+1\n+1\n+1\n+1\n+1\n=6","words":null}],"stats":{"pages":15,"words":158}}